{"type":"message","id":"fea0bea6","parentId":"93a02831","timestamp":"2026-03-26T19:27:34.601Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_0179qoQGpJ6GH3pzbKpHKgz5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) — Self-hosted, self-updating, self-aware (just kidding... unless?).\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --force-document       Send media as document to avoid Telegram compression\n                         (Telegram only). Applies to images and GIFs. (default:\n                         false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --interactive <json>   Shared interactive payload as JSON (buttons/selects\n                         rendered natively by supported channels)\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id\n  --silent               Send message silently without notification (Telegram +\n                         Discord) (default: false)\n  -t, --target <dest>    Recipient/channel: E.164 for WhatsApp/Signal, Telegram\n                         chat id/@username, Discord/Slack channel/user, or\n                         iMessage handle/chat_id\n  --thread-id <id>       Thread id (Telegram forum thread)\n  --verbose              Verbose logging (default: false)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1679,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) — Self-hosted, self-updating, self-aware (just kidding... unless?).\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --force-document       Send media as document to avoid Telegram compression\n                         (Telegram only). Applies to images and GIFs. (default:\n                         false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --interactive <json>   Shared interactive payload as JSON (buttons/selects\n                         rendered natively by supported channels)\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id\n  --silent               Send message silently without notification (Telegram +\n                         Discord) (default: false)\n  -t, --target <dest>    Recipient/channel: E.164 for WhatsApp/Signal, Telegram\n                         chat id/@username, Discord/Slack channel/user, or\n                         iMessage handle/chat_id\n  --thread-id <id>       Thread id (Telegram forum thread)\n  --verbose              Verbose logging (default: false)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774553254598}}
{"type":"message","id":"6bfa4b19","parentId":"fea0bea6","timestamp":"2026-03-26T19:27:44.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No hay opción `--agent`. Los mensajes salen siempre desde la cuenta principal. La única forma de que Ares aparezca como remitente en WhatsApp es que él tenga su propio número/cuenta de WhatsApp vinculado, lo cual requiere un número separado.\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Te hablo claro: **Ares no puede aparecer como remitente en WhatsApp** porque todos los agentes comparten el mismo número. El que envía siempre soy yo (Atlas) desde tu cuenta de WhatsApp.\n\nLo que sí se puede hacer:\n\n**Opción A — Yo envío al grupo identificándome como Ares**\nEl mensaje llega al grupo `Smart Project` desde tu número, pero escrito en voz de Ares con su identidad. Funcional y honesto.\n\n**Opción B — Ares tiene su propio número de WhatsApp**\nNecesitaría un número dedicado, vincularlo a OpenClaw y darle binding. Más trabajo pero sí quedaría como remitente separado.\n\nPara el entrenamiento de mañana, ¿envío yo al grupo en nombre de Ares ya mismo?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":288,"cacheRead":113516,"cacheWrite":609,"totalTokens":114414,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774553254602,"responseId":"msg_017nzF9XwADz1SdEBXLAtM5h"}}
